{
  "text": "For example, to justify drawing broader conclusions from a single-platform big data study, [CITATION_1] argue that analysis from a single platform, cell phone networks, is justified because, In many studies, for example, retweets or mentions are used for measuring \"influence.\" [CITATION_2] . A social media interaction may be a reasonable proxy for influence under certain conditions and times; however, there are many conceptual steps and implicit assumptions embedded in going from retweeting to being influenced. Most of the time, what is actually being measured is information exposure and/or reaction to information. The meaning of that retweet could range from affirmation to denunciation to sarcasm to approval to disgust.",
